The paper deals with finding heavy elements in streaming data, which is a classic problem in computer science. The focus is on the sliding window model, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to develop a polylogarithmic-memory algorithm. Additionally, the paper discusses applications to similarity estimation (cs.DB) and rarity estimation (cs.SI), which are related to database systems. Finally, the paper uses algorithmic techniques such as smooth histograms and exponential histograms, which are commonly used in algorithm design (cs.AL).
